<div data-type="problem" id="fs-id1170571699080">
<p id="fs-id1170571699083">Using precise definitions of limits, prove that <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><munder><mrow><mtext>lim</mtext></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">&#8594;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><munder><mrow><mtext>lim</mtext></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">&#8594;</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></munder><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> does not exist: <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><mo>{</mo><mtable columnalign="left"><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn><mspace width="0.2em"/><mtext>if</mtext><mspace width="0.2em"/><mi>x</mi><mspace width="0.2em"/><mtext>is rational</mtext></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn><mspace width="0.2em"/><mtext>if</mtext><mspace width="0.2em"/><mi>x</mi><mspace width="0.2em"/><mtext>is irrational</mtext></mtd></mtr></mtable></mrow><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><mo>{</mo><mtable columnalign="left"><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn><mspace width="0.2em"/><mtext>if</mtext><mspace width="0.2em"/><mi>x</mi><mspace width="0.2em"/><mtext>is rational</mtext></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn><mspace width="0.2em"/><mtext>if</mtext><mspace width="0.2em"/><mi>x</mi><mspace width="0.2em"/><mtext>is irrational</mtext></mtd></mtr></mtable></mrow><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> (<em data-effect="italics">Hint</em>: Think about how you can always choose a rational number <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>r</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>d</mi><mo>,</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Conte