<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-id1170571661071">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-id1170571661073">
<p id="fs-id1170571661075">Using the function from the previous exercise, use the precise definition of limits to show that <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><munder><mrow><mtext>lim</mtext></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">&#8594;</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></munder><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><munder><mrow><mtext>lim</mtext></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">&#8594;</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></munder><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> does not exist for <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>&#8800;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>&#8800;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></p>
</div>
</div>
<p id="fs-id1170571653014">For the following exercises, suppose that <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><munder><mrow><mtext>lim</mtext></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">&#8594;</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></munder><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mi>L</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><munder><mrow><mtext>lim</mtext></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">&#8594;</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></munder><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mi>L</mi></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> and <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><munder><mrow><mtext>lim</mtext></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">&#8594;</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></munder><mi>g</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mi>M</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><munder><mrow><mtext>lim</mtext></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">&#8594;</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></munder><mi>g</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mi>M</mi></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> both exist. Use the precise definition of limits to prove the following limit laws:</p>
<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-id1170571653079">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-id1170571653081">
<p id="fs-id1170571653083"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><munder><mrow><mtext>lim</mtext></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">&#8594;</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></munder><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>&#8722;</mo><mi>g</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mi>L</mi><mo>&#8722;</mo><mi>M</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><munder><mrow><mtext>lim</mtext></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">&#8594;</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></munder><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>&#8722;</mo><mi>g</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mi>L</mi><mo>&#8722;</mo><mi>M</mi></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></p>
</div>
<div data-type="solution" id="fs-id1170572293465">
<p id="fs-id1170572293467"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>&#8722;</mo><mi>g</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>+</mo><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mn>&#8722;1</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mi>g</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>&#8722;</mo><mi>g</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>+</mo><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mn>&#8722;1</mn></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mi>g</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></p>
</div>
</div>
<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-id1170571613536">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-id1170571613538">
<p id="fs-id1170571613540"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><munder><mrow><mtext>lim</mtext></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">&#8594;</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></munder><mrow><mo>[</mo><mrow><mi>c</mi><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>]</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mi>c</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><munder><mrow><mtext>lim</mtext></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">&#8594;</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></munder><mrow><mo>[</mo><mrow><mi>c</mi><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>]</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mi>c</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> for any real constant <em data-effect="italics">c</em> (<em data-effect="italics">Hint</em>: Consider two cases: <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> and <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mi>c</mi><mo>&#8800;</mo><mn>0</mn><mtext>.)</mtext></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mi>c</mi><mo>&#8800;</mo><mn>0</mn><mtext>.)</mtext></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></p>
</div>
</div>
<div data-type="exercise" id="fs-id1170571712568">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-id1170571712570">
<p id="fs-id1170571712572"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><munder><mrow><mtext>lim</mtext></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">&#8594;</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></munder><mrow><mo>[</mo><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mi>g</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>]</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mi>L</mi><mi>M</mi><mo>.</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><munder><mrow><mtext>lim</mtext></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo stretchy="false">&#8594;</mo><mi>a</mi></mrow></munder><mrow><mo>[</mo><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mi>g</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>]</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo><mi>L</mi><mi>M</mi><mo>.</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> (<em data-effect="italics">Hint</em>: <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mrow><mo>|</mo><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mi>g</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>&#8722;</mo><mi>L</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow><mo>|</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mrow><mo>|</mo><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mi>g</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>&#8722;</mo><mi>L</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow><mo>|</mo></mrow><mo>=</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><mo>|</mo><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mi>g</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>&#8722;</mo><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mi>M</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mi>M</mi><mo>&#8722;</mo><mi>L</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow><mo>|</mo></mrow><mo>&#8804;</mo><mrow><mo>|</mo><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>|</mo></mrow><mrow><mo>|</mo><mrow><mi>g</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>&#8722;</mo><mi>M</mi></mrow><mo>|</mo></mrow><mo>+</mo><mrow><mo>|</mo><mi>M</mi><mo>|</mo></mrow><mrow><mo>|</mo><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>&#8722;</mo><mi>L</mi></mrow><mo>|</mo><mtext>.)</mtext></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><mo>|</mo><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mi>g</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>&#8722;</mo><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mi>M</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mi>M</mi><mo>&#8722;</mo><mi>L</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow><mo>|</mo></mrow><mo>&#8804;</mo><mrow><mo>|</mo><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>|</mo></mrow><mrow><mo>|</mo><mrow><mi>g</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>&#8722;</mo><mi>M</mi></mrow><mo>|</mo></mrow><mo>+</mo><mrow><mo>|</mo><mi>M</mi><mo>|</mo></mrow><mrow><mo>|</mo><mrow><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>&#8722;</mo><mi>L</mi></mrow><mo>|</mo><mtext>.)</mtext></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math></p>
